review_text: Restoran cepat saji asli Indonesia ini sangat dicintai oleh banyak kalangan, mulai anak-anak sampai orang dewasa. Menunya beragam, dan yang jadi andalannya adalah ayam dengan saus pedasnya yang memeiliki tingkat kepedasan, mulai dari level 1 sampai 5. Bagi pelanggan yang jangan khawatir kepedasan, karena restoran ini menyediakan saus keju untuk mengurangi sensasi pedas di mulut. Minumannya yang paling ikonik adalah pink lava. Tata letak meja makan bisa outdoor dan indoor. Parkir cukup luas, bisa motor dan mobil. Toilet cukup bersih.
review_translated_text: This authentic Indonesian fast food restaurant is loved by many groups, from children to adults. The menu is varied, and the mainstay is chicken with spicy sauce which has a spiciness level, ranging from level 1 to 5. For customers who dont worry about spiciness, because this restaurant provides cheese sauce to reduce the spicy sensation in the mouth. Its most iconic drink is pink lava. The dining table layout can be outdoor and indoor. Parking is quite spacious, for motorbikes and cars. The toilet is quite clean.

review_translated_text: Sunday 7, April 2024 at 11:40 I ordered at Richesee Rungkut Madya Surabaya, I wanted to complain about the service which was not given a receipt, I ordered Fire combo 2x with lvl 0 breast size chicken all and pink lava less ice, a cashier served me with a dirty face maybe because I ordered right when it was closing, but in my opinion this was very disappointing, especially since I wasnt given a receipt at all and when I gave the product the other staff didnt check my order, I just gave them the product, please fix it immediately for the service and this is the last time I buy at Richesee Rungkut Madya Surabaya FYI, if you dont give a receipt, its usually free... thank you

review_text: Rasa makanan sudah psti enak ya semua taulah kalau richesse menjadi salah satu pencetus ayam hot lava di Indonesia.. namun alasan apa yang membuat saya memberikan nilai 3 pada tempat ini, mari kita urai : 1. Pelayanan sangat lama dan kurang ramah, ini adalah restorant yg menjual makanan fast food ( fast = cepat ), kalau lambat ini artinya sudah salah fatal. 2. Akses masuk ke parkiran tidak diperbaiki, jadi dari jalan masuk ke parkir ada seperti gundukan / lubang besar, kaget jga pdhl mobil saya suv monokok yg terkenal nyaman tpi terkena lubang dgn kecepatan 15kmh sampai goyang2, ini jd bwt saya ragu kesini lagi karena lama kelamaan understeel kaki2 mobil saya bisa bermasalah dan biayanya besar, mohon diperbaiki untuk akses masuknya, bayangkan kalau ad org pakai sedan / mobil yang dipendekan, saya rasa bakal hancur itu bumper. Hanya itu saja kekurangan dan masukan dari saya, untuk kualitas makanan, dan lain sebagainya bagus saja kecuali dua hal yg saya sebut dan urai diatas, terimakasih, sukses selalu
review_translated_text: The taste of the food is definitely delicious, yes everyone knows that Richesse is one of the originators of hot lava chicken in Indonesia... but what are the reasons that make me give this place a 3 score, lets explain: 1. The service is very long and not friendly, this is a restaurant that sells fast food (fast = fast), if it is slow this means something has gone wrong. 2. Access to the parking lot was not repaired, so from the entrance to the parking lot there was like a big bump/hole, I was also surprised even though my car was a monocoque SUV which is known to be comfortable but it hit a hole at a speed of 15 kmh until it was rocking, this is why Im hesitant to come here again because it takes a long time Over time, the understeel of my cars legs could become problematic and it would cost a lot of money, please repair it for access, imagine if someone used a sedan/car that was shortened, I think the bumper would be destroyed. Thats all the shortcomings and input from me, for the quality of the food, and so on, its good except for the two things I mentioned and explained above, thank you, always success

review_text: Salah satu cafe yang terletak di tengah Kota Sidoarjo, lokasinya ga terlalu jauh dari alun alun dan kantor pemerintahan. Pas di pinggir jalan raya. Suasananya cozy dengan banyak pilihan tempat duduk. Menunya juga lumayan beragam dengan kue dan pastrynya, kopi dan non-kopinya.. Kalau mau full-AC bisa duduk di lantai 1, kalau pun mau merokok bisa outdoor di lantai 2. Toiletnya juga ada di lantai 2. Parkiran agak terbatas ya, kalau mobil yang agak susah. Pembayaran bisa pakai tunai atau non tunai. Untuk harganya lumayan lah, cocok untuk kalangan menengah ke atas saja. Dietary restrictions: Porsinya sedikit cocok untuk diet Parking: Parkir motor yang lumayan, kalau mobil susah Kid-friendliness: Anak kecil kurang cocok Wheelchair accessibility: Agak susah yaa
review_translated_text: One of the cafes located in the middle of Sidoarjo City, the location is not too far from the main square and government offices. Right on the side of the highway. The atmosphere is cozy with lots of seating options. The menu is also quite varied with cakes and pastries, coffee and non-coffee... If you want full AC, you can sit on the 1st floor, if you want to smoke, you can go outdoors on the 2nd floor. The toilet is also on the 2nd floor. Parking is a bit limited, if you have a car its a bit difficult. Payment can be made using cash or non-cash. For the price, its not bad, suitable for the upper middle class only. Dietary restrictions: The portion is small, suitable for a diet Parking: Decent motorbike parking, if you have a car its difficult Kid-friendliness: Small children are not suitable Wheelchair accessibility: Its a bit difficult huh

Abah Choi mengambil lokasi strategis dengan berada di antara UMSIDA dan RSUD. With that being said, layout dari Abah Choi adalah memanjang kesamping. Karena itu, bagian dalamnya cukup luas dengan spot duduk memakai kursi maupun lesehan. Dari segi f&b, cukup banyak variasi makanan dan minuman yang harganya cukup standar dengan sistem pesan langsung bayar. Kamu dilarang membawa makanan dan minuman dari luar. Tersedia koneksi WiFi gratis tentunya dengan menanyakan ke kasir soal passwordnya. Untuk parkir, saya rasa cukup luas dan mudah. Namun akan sangat menjengkelkan jika kamu parkir di depan, dan di belakang motor kamu stuck tidak bisa keluar. Tidak ada tukang parkir karena parkir gratis.
response_from_owner_text: Hallo #kawanchoi. Terimakasih atas reviewnya. Yukk follow akun instagram @tac_choi agar tidak ketinggalan promo2 lainnya
review_translated_text: Abah Choi took a strategic location between UMSIDA and RSUD. With that being said, the layout of Abah Choi is stretched to the side. Because of this, the inside is quite spacious with seating spots using chairs or leishan. In terms of f&b, there are quite a lot of variations of food and drinks whose prices are quite standard with a direct pay order system. You are prohibited from bringing food and drinks from outside. Free WiFi connection is available of course by asking the cashier for the password. As for parking, I think its quite spacious and easy. However, it will be very annoying if you park in front, and at the back your motorbike is stuck and cant get out. There are no parking attendants because parking is free.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello #kawanchoi. Thank you for the review. Come on, follow the Instagram account @tac_choi so you dont miss other promotions

review_translated_text: Seriously, the food is all delicious. The place is nice and the service and drinks are a bit lacking. 1. When I entered (I was wearing the hijab) it seemed like a lot of people were looking at me, and it turned out that I just found out that it seemed like this place wasnt friendly, perhaps for people like that. 2. When I was at the cashier, it seemed like the boss didnt really understand what I meant, when I was asked do you want coffee or non-coffee I answered just ask for the sweet one, bro but the boss still insisted on his initial question, so I was forced to answer coffee. 3. We just finished ordering the drink, it turns out its ready. actually good. but when I drank half a glass, I realized there were flies. and I didnt want to drink anymore, so I asked my friend for a drink. eh, it turns out there are flies too. We feel strange... indeed we are outside, but it seems like there are only insects and mosquitoes. and didnt feel like there were flies stuck in our food/drinks, but suddenly there were dead flies in two of our drinks (it doesnt really make sense, sis) and the price of the drinks was quite expensive for me (around 28-30) for the delicious taste, but if The quality (cleanliness) is really poor if there are flies like this. I didnt dare take a photo of the fly in the drink because I was disgusted. I was no longer happy there and just decided to go back. 4. The parking fee is already included in the payment for food + drinks at the cafe, so I came with my friend (both girls) and the person (parking attendant) just stood there looking around (the person saw that we were having trouble reversing the motorbike). Its just so strange, we really have to ask for help first when the person is standing near us and take the initiative to reverse the motorbike where the layout is narrow. Thats my complaint, the owner is asked to check more often. Hopefully this doesnt happen to other visitors. Just made it a lesson, thank you. Parking: please take more initiative, sir, thank you

sebenernya udah lama kesini, tapi baru sempet review sekarang De jong adalah sebuah kafe minimalis di kota Sidoarjo dan terdapat ornamen/hiasan dinding yang sangat unik. indoornya kecil hanya ada beberapa meja dan kursi tapi tenang ada toilet kok. toilet nya juga bersih. waktu itu mendapat pelayanan yang ckup ramah. saya memesan churros untuk snack nya. tapi kenapa ya churros di sini tuh agak lembek teksturnya jadinya mirip cakwe tapi lebih halus gitu aja sii. saos cocolannya juga bukan coklat yang dicairkan melainkan karamel. udah berekspektasi tinggi sih waktu itu tk kirain churrosnya crispy gitu dan saos cocolannya coklat seperti yang dijual di mall2. untuk harga standard cafe lah ya, mohon  diperbaiki  untuk resep churrosnya agar pelanggan tidak berekspektasi tinggi. dan oiya satu lagi teruntuk staff de jong, apabila ada customer yang sedang me time mbok ya jangan diperhatiin trs sembari sering ditatap gitu. saya agak risih jadinya, padahal niatnya cuma nyelesaikan kerjaan kok. tk lihat-lihat penampilan saya juga ndak aneh , agak gemes sii kalo kedapatan kafe dengan staff yang seperti ini. selebihnya kafe ini patut dicoba kok bagi yang penasaran sama vibe nya. but, repurchase? noo. mohon maaf apabila penilaian saya ada yang kurang berkenan di hati kalian teruntuk para staff dan owner de jong. penilaian ini saya tulis berdasarkan pengalaman saya sewaktu mengunjungi kafe ini. Sukses selalu
review_translated_text: Ive actually been here for a long time, but I just had the chance to review it now De Jong is a minimalist cafe in the city of Sidoarjo and has very unique wall decorations/ornaments. The indoor area is small, there are only a few tables and chairs, but dont worry, there is a toilet. the toilet is also clean. At that time the service was quite friendly. I ordered churros as a snack. But why is it that the churros here are a bit soft, the texture is similar to cakwe but smoother, thats all. The dipping sauce is also not melted chocolate but caramel. I had high expectations at that time, but I didnt expect the churros to be so crispy and the dipping sauce to be chocolate like those sold in malls. For standard cafe prices, please improve the churros recipe so that customers dont have high expectations. And oh yes, one more thing for De Jongs staff, if there are customers who are having me time, dont pay attention to them and often stare at them like that. I felt a bit uncomfortable, even though my intention was just to finish the work. If I look around, my appearance isnt strange, Id be a bit annoyed if I found a cafe with staff like this. Otherwise, this cafe is worth a try for those who are curious about its vibe. but, repurchase? noo. Im sorry if my assessment is something you dont like, the staff and owner of De Jong. I wrote this assessment based on my experience when visiting this cafe. Always success

review_text: LOCATION: Lokasi strategis dipinggir jalan utama. Terletak di area ruko sebelah brand Haus. Tempat parkirnya cukup banyak terutama untuk   sepeda motor dan agak sulit untuk   mobil. VIBES: Interiornya standar seperti Kopi Kenangan di outlet pada umumnya. Terdapat 2 lantai dengan ruang indoor dan outdoor. Tempat ini cocok untuk para introvert yang ingin me time atau sekedar nongkrong dengan orang   dan cocok juga untuk produktif  . AC-nya juga cukup dingin saat berkunjung kesini. Tapi tempatnya tidak begitu besar. PRICE & TASTE: Harga masih terjangkau  . Pembayaran bisa cash atau QRIS. Lebih murah pembelian lewat aplikasi    KOPI KENANGAN lebih murah, kadang ada promo voucher & cashback. Menunya cukup beragam. Rasa kopinya   Juara dan   rotinya juga enak banget . FACILITIES: WIFI akhirnya tersedia saat berkunjung dibulan ini pada Oktober 2023 ini sebelumnya belum tersedia. Untuk saat ini kecepatannya oke karena WIFI.ID cukup trusted untuk kecepatan stabil. kamar mandi bersih. Tersedia Mushola untuk 1 orang. Ada charging spacenya namun tidak banyak. MORE REVIEW: Overall, mulai ada peningkatan dan menunya mulai cukup beragam. akhirnya udah ada WIFI nya jadi yang biasa nya hanya takeaway sekarang bisa bersantai sejenak di sini. Barista nya juga ramah.
review_translated_text: LOCATION: Strategic location next to the main road. Located in the shophouse area next to the Haus brand. There is quite a lot of parking, especially for   motorbikes and a bit difficult for   cars. VIBES: The interior is standard like Kopi Kenangan in general outlets. There are 2 floors with indoor and outdoor space. This place is suitable for introverts who want to have me time or just hang out with people   and is also suitable for being productive  . The AC was also quite cold when visiting here. But the place is not that big. PRICE & TASTE: Prices are still affordable  . Payment can be cash or QRIS. Its cheaper to purchase via the application   COFFEE KENINGANGAN is cheaper, sometimes there are voucher & cashback promos. The menu is quite diverse. The coffee tastes   Champion and   the bread is also really delicious  . FACILITIES: WIFI is finally available when visiting this month in October 2023, previously it was not available. For now the speed is okay because WIFI.ID is trusted enough for stable speeds. clean bathroom. Prayer room available for 1 person. There is charging space but not much. MORE REVIEWS: Overall, there are starting to be improvements and the menu is starting to be quite diverse. Finally there is WIFI so those who usually just takeaway can now relax for a moment here. The barista is also friendly.

review_text: Hai para Local Guides! Kali pertama ini bikin meetup. Sebelum mulai recap nya, makasih dulu buat Roro yang bikinin meetup di localguide (karena ga sempat bikin pas itu. hahaha) Ismi yang menjadi MC, dan seluruh Local Guides yang sudah hadir di FoodCrawl kali ini. FoodCrawl Local Guides Surabaya tgl 30 Oktober 2017 merupakan kolaborasi bersama Risolive Cafetaria yang beralamat di Jl. Gayungsari Tim. IV Blok MGK-01 Surabaya. FoodCrawl kali ini dihadiri oleh 20 Local Guides yang berasal dari Surabaya dan Sidoarjo. Seperti biasa kami perkenalan satu persatu karena banyak juga teman-teman baru, penjelasan tentang masakan oleh koki Risolive Cafetaria, dan foto-foto. Tidak lupa juga untuk mengabadikan momen kolaborasi Local Guides Surabaya dengan Risolive Cafetaria Sekilas tentang Risolive Cafetaria, bermula dari usaha rumah yang  kebanjiran  order risoles, akhirnya mereka membuka bisnis kuliner. Meski baru dimulai pada awal tahun 2017, Risolive Cafetaria perlahan dikenal masyarakat. Ga hanya menyajikan risoles andalan mereka, tapi juga makanan dan minuman hasil racikan resep pribadi, membuat rasa masakannya unik seperti Dory Sambal Matah, Salted Egg Chicken, bahkan ada minuman gabungan bernama Es Degan Lombok yang rasanya ada semriwingnya! Sampai ketemu di acara berikutnya ya!
review_translated_text: Hi Local Guides! This is the first time holding a meetup. Before starting the recap, thank you first to Roro who made the meetup at localguide (because I didnt have time to make it right. hahaha) Ismi who was the MC, and all the Local Guides who were present at FoodCrawl this time. FoodCrawl Local Guides Surabaya on 30 October 2017 is a collaboration with Risolive Cafetaria which is located at Jl. Gayungsari Team. IV Block MGK-01 Surabaya. This time, FoodCrawl was attended by 20 Local Guides from Surabaya and Sidoarjo. As usual, we introduced each other one by one because there were lots of new friends, explained the dishes by the Risolive Cafetaria chef, and took photos. Dont forget to capture the moment of collaboration between Local Guides Surabaya and Risolive Cafetaria A glimpse of Risolive Cafetaria, starting from a home business that was flooded with orders for risoles, they finally opened a culinary business. Even though it only started at the beginning of 2017, Risolive Cafetaria is slowly becoming known to the public. Not only do they serve their flagship rissoles, but also food and drinks made from personal recipes, making the taste of the dishes unique, such as Dory Sambal Matah, Salted Egg Chicken, there is even a combined drink called Es Degan Lombok which tastes delicious! See you at the next event!

For the taste, its good according to the price, the place is also nice, breezy. the minus is the service. The table still has lots of used plates/glasses that havent been cleaned, theres not enough satset. You should prioritize the tables that are displayed, clean them, put them in the kitchen first, so people can see them. In fact, what really disappointed me was, I ate at a table that still had other peoples plates/glasses left on it, when my food came, the lady/madam should have taken the glass/plate. but not even that, just leave it alone. wheres the manner? You can see the photo listed. it says on the website that it closes at 22.00 WIB, but when someone asks at 21.00 it says its already closed, so I think it might be busy so its likely to run out quickly, so if it has to close quickly. But whats really unfortunate is, there are people asking Is it still there? I just said to mba, Isnt that enough? Sis and bro are also tired, are they nervous about closing up? Haha thats all, thx u. response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih kak utk reviewnya.  Namun ada beberapa point yg mungkin perlu kami luruskan disini: 1. Untuk makanan, range harga berkisar 20rb-30rb an per PORSI /orang, dimana porsi banyak/sedikit, mahal/murah itu relatif. Dari segi porsi makanan, rasa, bahan baku yg dipakai semua bersih dan terjaga kualitasnya. Tempat kami juga memakai AC seperti yg kakak sebutkan tadi, kalau tempat kami NYAMAN. Jadi wajar saja dengan konsep rice bowl, makan dan duduk nyaman di tempat ber AC, jika per porsi seharga 20rb-30rb an /orang. Tapi kami bisa pastikan, kalau makanan kami pasti enak, berkualitas, dan mengenyangkan. 2. Gambar dan kenyataan tidak sama hal ini menurut kami tidak valid. Kami memakai jasa fotografer dan pemotretan makanan dilakukan di studio, dengan lighting dsb. Dengan adanya hal tsb, tentu saja kami mengharapkan dan mengusahakan hasil foto yg terbaik untuk memasarkan makanan yg kami jual, sama seperti cafe2 lainnya. Disini kami pastikan, bahwa semua makanan pada foto & video, adalah product yg kami jual sebenar2nya, baik volume makanan per porsi, dan juga kualitas makanan di foto dan yg kami jual, semuanya tidak dibedakan. 3. Untuk reviewer dan pembaca, boleh datang dan rasakan langsung, untuk menilai sendiri rasa dan kualitas dari makanan kami, kami yakin experience dari rasa makanan kami tidak akan mengecewakan. Terbukti nyata, tidak sedikit customer kami yg sering repeat order. Thank You
review_translated_text: The food is really expensive... Wheres the smaller portion? If its for college kids, its enough, just go there once Picture and reality are not the same, Seriously.. The service at the front is ok, the atmosphere is comfortable, but the food menu is not good For those of you who have already sat down, its better to just hurry back, or if you want to be disappointed, just try it first. I suggest its better or not
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you sis for the review. However, there are several points that we might need to clarify here: 1. For food, the price range is around 20 thousand-30 thousand per PORTION / person, where portions are large/small, expensive/cheap are relative. In terms of food portions, taste, raw materials used, everything is clean and the quality is maintained. Our place also uses AC as you mentioned earlier, our place is COMFORTABLE. So its only natural with the rice bowl concept, eating and sitting comfortably in an air-conditioned place, if each portion costs around 20 thousand-30 thousand per person. But we can guarantee that our food will be delicious, high quality and filling. 2. Image and reality are not the same in our opinion this is not valid. We use the services of a photographer and food photography is done in a studio, with lighting, etc. With this in mind, of course we hope and strive for the best photos to market the food we sell, just like other cafes. Here we ensure that all the food in the photos & videos is the actual product that we sell, both the volume of food per portion, and also the quality of the food in the photos and what we sell, everything is not differentiated. 3. For reviewers and readers, you are welcome to come and taste it directly, to judge for yourself the taste and quality of our food, we are sure that the experience of the taste of our food will not disappoint. It has been proven that quite a few of our customers often repeat orders. Thank you

review_translated_text: Hanging out here on weekends eating ramen. I thought the ramen place was different from the cafe, but it turns out they are one. Fast service, drinks are served first and then the ramen. The service members were quick to clean the outdoor tables and chairs which were wet because of the drizzle. The taste of the ramen is delicious, the portion is filling and the soup is quite flavorful and tasty. Compared to other ramen in the city of Sidoarjo, this is one of the ramen that is worth buying, apart from the affordable price. As for the lychee iced tea, I didnt expect there to be real lychees, the combination of tea and lychee flavors is really fresh. But as for the vibe of the place, its just normal, its supported by live music so its ok. Parking is also spacious, there is a lot of car parking because there is an empty lot next to the cafe. But I will definitely come back here if I want ramen   I want to try other menus and the coffee too ;)

Maaf bintang 3 karena menu standar tapi mahal Pesan Cappuccino, kukira manual brew. Tapi kalau dirasa2 tadi seperti minuman instan sachet gitu2. Makanannya banyak yang ga ready. Tadi pas di pesen kayak tebak2an menu sama mbak2 kasir. Mau pesan Nasi A, ternyata ga ready. Dijelaskan yg ada cuma nasi BCDE. Terus mau Mie kuah pake telor, gaada juga. Dijelaskan yang ada cuma menu dimsum, itupun cuma beberapa yg ready stock. Tapi lagi ga pengen dimsum. Skip. Terus aku tanya lagi, roti bakarnya ada? Ga ada juga. French fries ada? Ga ada juga. Terus dijelaskan yang ada cuma burger, cireng, dan pisang2an. Akhirnya pesen cireng. Dengan harga segitu ekspektasi saya lumayan tinggi qty cireng yang akan disajikan. Eh yaallah ternyata sedikit sekali porsinya :( Ya intinya mohon maaf. Namanya juga mengulas hehe Lalu dari segi fasilitas. Jumlah tempat duduk terlalu sedikit. Dan lantai 2 cuma ditopang sama besi kayak kanopi gitu apasi namanya gatau, pokoknya pas ada pengunjung jalan di lt. 2 jatuhnya berisik : Jadi buat kalian yang kesini niatnya pengen nugas atau me time atau pengen duduk2 di warung tp yang tenang, sepertinya kurang cocok kalau ke Nom2an. Disini juga ada toilet dan mushola. Parkir lumayan ~ Bagusnya, disini pelayanannya cepet. Ga nunggu lama. Terimakasih.
review_translated_text: Sorry for the 3 stars because the menu is standard but expensive Order Cappuccino, I think manual brew. But if you taste it, its like an instant drink sachet. Many of the foods are not ready. When I ordered, it was like the cashier was guessing about the menu. Want to order Nasi A, apparently its not ready. It was explained that there was only BCDE rice. Then I wanted noodle soup with egg, but I didnt have any. It was explained that there was only a dimsum menu, and even then only a few were ready stock. But I dont want dim sum anymore. Skip. Then I asked again, is there toast? There arent any either. Are there French fries? There arent any either. Then he explained that the only thing available was burgers, cireng and bananas. Finally ordered cireng. With that price, my expectations are quite high for the qty of cireng that will be served. Oh my God, it turns out the portion is so small :( Yes, basically Im sorry. The name is also a review hehe Then in terms of facilities. The number of seats is too few. And the 2nd floor is only supported by iron like a canopy, I dont know what its called, basically when there are visitors walking on the floor. 2 noisy falls : So for those of you who come here with the intention of doing homework or me time or wanting to sit in a cafe but its quiet, it doesnt seem suitable to go to Nom2an. There are also toilets and prayer rooms here. Parking is decent~ The good thing is, the service here is fast. Dont wait long. Thank You.

The cafe here is very spacious, consisting of a 3-story building and the cafe is on floors 1 and 3. To order food, there are various kinds, from snacks, Korean food, gelato, dimsum, to heavy food. Drinks include tea, coffee, non-coffee and beer. The service is very friendly, the cashier is also nice, you can pay with QRIS, there is live music and the parking is spacious. There is wifi and plugs, on the 3rd floor there is an outdoor and indoor garden. review_text: Berkunjung di H+1 lebaran, cukup ramai walau tidak sampai yang penuh banget area makannya. Untuk baksonya sistemnya ambil sendiri lalu bayar di kasir. Untuk menu lain seperti ayam, iga, cwie mie, snack, kopi, dan minuman pesan di kasir. Pelayanannya waktu itu agak lama, baik itu buat ngerefill bakso yang habis, nganter pesanan, dan juga bersihin meja kotor. Mungkin karena ada staff yg masih libur. Kami pesan bakso, cwi mie, dan ayam penyet. Rasa makanannya overall enak sih. Ayam penyetnya bumbu meresap ke dalam. Cwi mie standar, tapi topping ayamnya banyak. Bakso cukup nge daging dengan kuah gurih light. Suasana tempatnya seperti cafe, tidak seperti warung bakso. Area makan cukup luas, lantai 1 dan 2. Di lt 2 ada private room nya juga. Toilet di lt.1 dan lt.3. Musholla di lt.3. Parkir mobil juga cukup luas.
review_translated_text: Visiting on H+1 of Eid, it was quite busy although the eating area wasnt completely full. For the meatballs, the system is to pick it up yourself then pay at the cashier. For other menus such as chicken, ribs, cwie noodles, snacks, coffee and drinks, order at the cashier. The service at that time took a bit of time, both for refilling the meatballs that had run out, delivering orders, and also cleaning dirty tables. Maybe because there are staff who are still on holiday. We ordered meatballs, cwi noodles and chicken penyet. Overall the taste of the food is delicious. The spices seep into the chicken penyet. Standard cwi noodles, but lots of chicken toppings. The meatballs are quite meaty with a light savory sauce. The atmosphere of the place is like a cafe, not like a meatball shop. The dining area is quite spacious, floors 1 and 2. On the 2nd floor there is a private room too. Toilets on 1st floor and 3rd floor. Prayer room on 3rd floor. Car parking is also quite spacious.

review_text: Bakso Cak To berlokasi di JL Pahlawan - Sidoarjo. Pas Embong bundar ponti. Seberang McD Sidoarjo. Lokasi sangat strategis parkiran gak terlalu luas. Tempat baksonya di lantai 2 untuk lantai 1 nya ada cafe. Tempat bagus dan unik, untuk segi rasa kuah baksonya segar tapi kurang sedap harus tambah garam dikit. Untuk rasa Baksonya  urat, keju, mercon, tahu bakso, gorengan lumaya enak dan berasa, tapi untuk bakso halusnya gak ada rasanya hambar banget. Untuk harga standart sih. Pelayanan cepat karena pas sepi pengunjung. Tersedia toilet dan mushola dilantai 3.
review_translated_text: Bakso Cak To is located at JL Pahlawan - Sidoarjo. Fitting Embong round ponti. Opposite McD Sidoarjo. Very strategic location, parking is not too wide. The meatball place is on the 2nd floor and on the 1st floor there is a cafe. Nice and unique place, in terms of taste the meatball sauce is fresh but not delicious, you have to add a little salt. In terms of taste, the beef meatballs, cheese, firecrackers, tofu meatballs, fried meatballs are quite delicious and tasteful, but the soft meatballs dont have a very bland taste. For standard prices anyway. Fast service because there are few visitors. There are toilets and a prayer room on the 3rd floor.

review_text: Bakso Cak To berada di seberang McD Sidoarjo. Terletak di lantai 2, atas jungkir balik cafe. Utk tempat di Bakso Cak To ini luas, bersih dan nyaman. Viewnya pun menarik. Utk harga lumayan pricey dibandingkan bakso yg memiliki varian pentol serupa dengan bakso cak to. Utk rasa lumayan menurut saya. Banyak varian pentol yang tersedia di sini mulai dari puyuh, keju, mercon, halus dsbnya. Pentol merconnya kurang pedes sih Sistemnya prasmanan jd ambil mangkok sendiri kita isi sesuka hati. Kemudian dibayar dan dituangkan kuah oleh pegawainya. Taburannya juga lengkap bisa perasan jeruk, koya dan ijo2. So lumayan recomended apalagi untuk kunpul2
review_translated_text: Bakso Cak To is opposite McD Sidoarjo. Located on the 2nd floor, above the somersault cafe. The place at Bakso Cak To is spacious, clean and comfortable. The view is also interesting. The price is quite pricey compared to meatballs which have a pentol variant similar to Cak To meatballs. For the taste, its pretty good in my opinion. There are many variations of pentol available here, ranging from quail, cheese, firecracker, smooth, etc. The firecracker bulb isnt spicy enough The system is a buffet so we take our own bowl and fill it to our hearts content. Then the employee paid and poured the sauce. The toppings are also complete, including orange juice, koya and ijo2. So its quite recommended, especially for kunpul2

review_text: Undoubtedly, they are true coffee crafters! Both their espresso-based and manual brews are top quality. Personally, I cant get enough of their dark roast cappuccino, its hands down one of the best in Surabaya! And with their curated coffee beans lineup, regularly refreshed, theres always something new and interesting to try. Oh, and their innovative coffee mocktails? Absolutely delightful! But its not just about the coffee, its the whole atmosphere too. The hospitality is really welcoming and warm, the staff is super kind and friendly, and also knowledgeable about coffee - they are always ready to share some coffee insights and suggestions or satisfy any special requests (Taaasty mocha makasih  ). Then, the places minimalist Japanese zen design makes it so aesthetically pleasing, relaxing, and cozy. *Bonus: Its never too crowded, making it the perfect spot to unwind and enjoy a good cup of coffee after a long days work. Thats why it became my go-to coffee shop during the week! Its a hidden gem for coffee lovers in east Surabaya. You will be missed guys :( ... terima kasih banyak for all the good times and consistently amazing coffee!

Mendeskripsikan warkop (Surabaya style) sebenarnya ga perlu terlalu panjang lebar, karena sejatinya warkop yang biasa ditemui di jalanan di Kota Surabaya pada dasarnya akan sama. Mereka sedia beragam minuman sachet dari kekopian sampai nenutrisarian, sedia indomie, dan koneksi wifi gratis speed seadanya untuk menemani kesendirianmu. Tapi karena ini saya yang mereview, dan saya biasa bercerita di review saya. Maka jadinya ini akan menjadi tulisan yang agak panjang. Warkop Karambol ini cukup straightforward seperti warkop-warkop lainnya. Jadi spesial karena namanya Karambol, sebuah permainan jadul yang menggunakan alat berbentuk papan dan kepingan-kepingan mika sebagai buahnya. Kalo pingin tahu detil karambol, silakan googling sendiri. Nah, sebelumnya warkop ini menyediakan beberapa papan karambol sebagai penarik tamunya. Permainan ini sangat menyenangkan jika dimainkan bersama-sama. Namun, seiring perkembangan gadget dan game mobile, sepertinya peminat karambol menjadi surut. Hasilnya, papan karambolnya sudah disingkirkan oleh pemilik, tinggal namanya aja yang tetap dipertahankan. Bisnis sampingan pemilik warkop ini sangat menarik. Jika kamu berkunjung ke warkop ini, kamu akan disambut dengan beberapa aquarium yang ditata rapi di sudut warkop. Yep, bisnis sampingannya adalah jualan ikan hias dan aquarium. Adanya tatanan aquarium di sini menjadi gimmick warkop yang khas, dan pengunjung pun bisa menikmati pemandangan ikan-ikan hias yang berenang kesana kemari. Monggo kalo kamu berada di area wonorejo dan sekitarnya kalo mau berhenti sejenak dan meneguk minuman sachet favoritmu di sini.

review_translated_text: Describing warkop (Surabaya style) actually doesnt need to be too long, because in fact the warkops that are usually found on the streets of Surabaya City are basically the same. They provide a variety of sachet drinks from coffee to nenutrisarian, provide Indomie, and a free WiFi connection with minimal speed to accompany your solitude. But because this is me reviewing, and I usually tell stories in my reviews. So this will be a rather long article. Warkop Karom is quite straightforward like other warkops. Its special because its called Karambol, an old school game that uses a board-shaped tool and pieces of mica as the fruit. If you want to know the details of carrom, please google it yourself. Well, previously this warkop provided several carrom boards to attract guests. This game is very fun if played together. However, along with the development of gadgets and mobile games, it seems that interest in carom has receded. As a result, the carom board has been removed by the owner, only the name remains. This warkop owners side business is very interesting. If you visit this warkop, you will be greeted with several aquariums neatly arranged in the corner of the warkop. Yep, his side business is selling ornamental and aquarium fish. The aquarium setup here is a typical warkop gimmick, and visitors can enjoy the view of ornamental fish swimming here and there. Please, if you are in the Wonorejo area and surrounding areas, if you want to stop for a moment and sip your favorite sachet drink here.

Cuma sayang kayaknya kurang mateng dikit jadi masih alot. Alhasil ga aku habisin hiks. review_translated_text: The place is really beautiful  but its a bit uncomfortable on the sofa against the wall because the table is too high. Im more suited to sitting in a single chair, right next to the table. As for the food, it tastes really good, rich flavour. Not the bland one. Buy red velvet cake, fettucini carbonara and mojito berries. Everything is delicious   red velvet is a type of cream cheese that is thick and really delicious. The bread is dense, makes you full. Carbonara is delicious, the taste is a balance between the cheese and onions. It also feels right. Its just a shame it seems like its not cooked a bit so its still tough. As a result I didnt finish it sob. As for the mojito, its delicious, fresh, the fruit isnt stingy but it turns out its not a suitable combination to drink with carbonara :) but definitely will come here again to try the other menu

review_text: Kalau pas pengen ngabur sendirian, ini bisa jadi alternatif sih buat duduk berjam - jam sambil laptopan. Cafenya terletak di kawasan perumahan asri yang notabene juga ngga terlalu banyak kendaraan sliweran. Trus juga mudah ditemukan dan sesuai sama petunjuk yang ada di Google Maps. Untuk pembayarannya, di Omi Cafe menyediakan beberapa opsi : Tunai, QRis, dan Debit. Jadi ngga perlu khawatir bingung tarik tunai karena ngga bawa cash. Disini ada 2 ruangan besar dengan kapasitas maksimal 20 orang (di lantai 2) dan 50 orang (di lantai 1) yang bisa jadi opsi buat event specialmu. Sewa tempatnya free, dengan minimal pembelian 30rb/pax. Tenang aja, disini ngga cuma ada cake dan menu - menu lucu aja kok. Makanan berat seperti nasi goreng, mie goreng, rice bowl, hingga ke camilan nusantara seperti cireng, pisang coklat, french fries, salad buah, juga tersedia disini. Udah okey banget buat makan cantik. Ambience tempatnya nyaman, kursinya bersih, rapi, dan selalu tersedia fresh flowers tiap disana. Selalu ganti - ganti bunga mejanya. Jadi berasa kayak diapresiasi gitu ngga sih tiap kesini tuuu... Toiletnya bersih, ada mushola mininya di lantai 2 (tempat sholat timnya), trus area parkirnya juga luas. Biaya parkirnya? Rp 0,-, karena emang ngga ada tukang parkirnya. Meskipun begitu, kamu tetep bisa pantau kendaraanmu dengan baik kok, karena tersedia kaca besar antara ruangan dengan area parkir. Tetep bisa ngintip! So far, tiap aku lagi sedih, lagi pengen makan - makanan manis, lagi cari inspirasi, nih tempat jadi salah satu tempat pelarianku selama stay di Sidoarjo.. Thankyou ya Omi Cafe ^^
review_translated_text: If you want to escape alone, this could be an alternative to sitting for hours on your laptop. The cafe is located in a beautiful residential area which incidentally doesnt have too many vehicles passing by. Then its also easy to find and matches the instructions on Google Maps. For payment, Omi Cafe provides several options: Cash, QRis, and Debit. So you dont need to worry about being confused about withdrawing cash because you dont have cash with you. Here there are 2 large rooms with a maximum capacity of 20 people (on the 2nd floor) and 50 people (on the 1st floor) which could be an option for your special event. Renting the place is free, with a minimum purchase of IDR 30 thousand/pax. Dont worry, there arent just cakes and cute menus here. Heavy foods such as fried rice, fried noodles, rice bowls, even Indonesian snacks such as cireng, chocolate bananas, french fries, fruit salad, are also available here. Its really good for eating pretty. The atmosphere of the place is comfortable, the chairs are clean, neat, and fresh flowers are always available every time there. Always change the table flowers. So it feels like Im being appreciated every time I come here... The toilets are clean, there is a mini prayer room on the 2nd floor (where the team prays), and the parking area is also spacious. The parking fee? IDR 0,-, because there is no parking attendant. Even so, you can still monitor your vehicle well, because there is a large mirror between the room and the parking area. You can still peek! So far, every time Im sad, want to eat sweet food, looking for inspiration, this place is one of my escape spots while staying in Sidoarjo... Thank you, Omi Cafe ^^

VIBES: Interiornya cukup bagus dan terlihat lebih niat dari franchise Janji Jiwa yang lain di Surabaya. Tersedia indoor dan outdoor area. AC-nya dingin apalagi di malam hari. Banyak meja yang tersedia di gerai ini. Mudah di gunakan untuk Cocok di gunakan untuk meetup, productive, nugas, rapat, terutama untuk mahasiswa. Namun terkadang kurang nyaman disaat ramai karena Sebagian besar customer nya pelajar tentu cukup ribut. PRICE & TASTE: Harga murah apalagi pakai    aplikasi Jiwa+ banyak promo maupun voucher discount yang menarik  .  Pembayaran bisa Tunai maupun via E-money. Menunya cukup beragam, rasa minumannya standard namun terkadang kualitas   coffee nya kadang kurang konsisten, kadang oke, kadang kurang. Untuk toast nya masih oke. FACILITIES: WIFI tersedia tetapi kecepatan agak tidak konsisten, kadang baik dan kadang buruk. kadang kamar mandinya bersih, kadang tidak. Charging Space nya sangat ramah dan banyak spot tersedia. Tidak ada Mushola MORE REVIEW: Overall kalau bandingkan dengan Janji Jiwa di Surabaya ini yang paling bagus  JJ358 pelayanan ramah dan cepat. Namun kualitas rasanya masih kurang. Awal nya buka 24 jam sekarang hanya dari jam 7 pagi   hingga 10 malam . Sejujurnya kalau agak malam indoor nya banyak nyamuk, mungkin dari pihak Coffee shop nya bisa di cari solusi untuk mengatasi nya. Selain itu, saya berharap pengunjung   lebih aware apa itu self-service dan bisa membuang sampah   sebelum meninggalkan lokasi. Overall masih bagus untuk dikunjungi.
review_translated_text: LOCATION: Strategic location next to the main road. There is quite a lot of parking, especially   motorbikes. VIBES: The interior is quite nice and looks more intentional than the other Janji Jiwa franchise in Surabaya. Indoor and outdoor areas are available. The AC is cold, especially at night. Many tables are available at this outlet. Easy to use for Suitable for use for meetups, productivity, assignments, meetings, especially for students. However, sometimes its uncomfortable when its busy because most of the customers are students and are quite noisy. PRICE & TASTE: Cheap prices, especially using the Jiwa+ application, lots of attractive promos and discount vouchers  . Payment can be cash or via e-money. The menu is quite diverse, the taste of the drinks is standard but sometimes the quality of the  coffee is sometimes inconsistent, sometimes okay, sometimes not enough. The toast is still okay. FACILITIES: WIFI is available but speed is a bit inconsistent, sometimes good and sometimes bad. sometimes the bathroom is clean, sometimes not. The charging space is very friendly and there are lots of spots available. There is no prayer room MORE REVIEWS: Overall, if you compare it with Janji Jiwa in Surabaya, this is the best  JJ358 friendly and fast service. However, the quality of the taste is still lacking. Initially it was open 24 hours now only from 7 am   to 10 pm  . To be honest, if there are a lot of mosquitoes indoors at night, maybe the coffee shop can find a solution to overcome this. Apart from that, I hope that visitors   are more aware of what self-service is and can throw away rubbish   before leaving the location. Overall its still a good place to visit.

review_text: Cafe Kopi Janji Jiwa ini letaknya sangat sangat strategis, pas di pinggir jalan sangat besar dan terlihat bagus. Kedai janji jiwa ini terdiri dari 2 lantai dan sangat luas di dalamnya. Lantai 1 full AC, lantai 2 ada AC dan Non AC. Pelayanannya sangat ramah dan cepat, ada aneka minuman mulai dari Kopi, teh, susu dan ada juga makanan seperti roti dan kentang. Untuk harga cukup bersahabat karena memang sering ada banyak promo. Rasanya jelas enak Hampir semua meja ada colokan, wifi lumayan cepat jika sepi namun jika mulai ramai akan melambat. Di lantai 2 sayangnya Wifinya tidak bisa mungkin karena susah signal. Vegetarian options: Ada sayurnya Dietary restrictions: Bisa beli minuman saja Parking: Parkir luas di depan cafe Kid-friendliness: Ada menu non kopi Wheelchair accessibility: Kursi roda bisa masuk di lantai 1
review_translated_text: The Janji Jiwa Coffee Cafe is very strategically located, right on the side of the road, it is very big and looks nice. This Jiwa Promise shop consists of 2 floors and is very spacious inside. The 1st floor is fully AC, the 2nd floor is AC and non-AC. The service is very friendly and fast, there are various drinks ranging from coffee, tea, milk and there are also foods such as bread and potatoes. The prices are quite friendly because there are often lots of promotions. It definitely tastes good Almost all tables have plugs, wifi is quite fast when its quiet but if it starts to get busy it will slow down. On the 2nd floor, unfortunately the WiFi is not possible because the signal is difficult. Vegetarian options: There are vegetables Dietary restrictions: You can just buy drinks Parking: Ample parking in front of the cafe Kid-friendliness: There is a non-coffee menu Wheelchair accessibility: Wheelchairs can be entered on the 1st floor

review_text: Lokasi Janji Jiwa & Jiwa Toast ini strategis karena dikelilingi perumahan, dekat kawasan industri dan beberapa sekolah + kampus Suasana weekend pagi-siang hari cukup ramai, namun masih nyaman digunakan utk urus kerjaan. Tempat untuk pengunjung ada bermacam-macam variasi: Dudukan sofa, kursi tinggi, kursi makan biasa, indoor maupun outdoor. Sesuaikan dengan kebutuhan saja, yang penting nyaman. AC nya adem banget, mungkin karena faktor mendung juga. Petugasnya ramah dan profesional, hanya saja crewnya kadang kewalahan ketika orderan online lagi banyak-banyaknya, pengunjung onsite terpaksa antri lebih lama. Uniknya, tempat ini tidak menerima pembayaran tunai. Wajib pakai kartu (debit/kredit) atau qris. Ada fasilitas free wifi juga, bisa minta infonya ke petugas/kasir kalau mau pakai wifi janji jiwa. Dari segi menu... tidak perlu ditanya lagi, sip lah. Suka sama pilihan susu utk beberapa menu minumannya, boleh pilih soy atau oat milk. Bagi yang ingin sholat, solusinya perlu ke masjid terdekat, salah satu pilihannya Masjid Ash-Shobiriin di seberang mie mapan. Sekitar 1-2 menit dari janji jiwa kalau naik mtor Parking: Parkiran cukup memadai dibandingkan kapasitas pengunjung
review_translated_text: The location of Janji Jiwa & Jiwa Toast is strategic because it is surrounded by housing, near industrial areas and several schools + campuses The weekend atmosphere is quite busy in the morning and afternoon, but it is still comfortable to use to take care of work. There are various variations of places for visitors: sofas, high chairs, regular dining chairs, indoor and outdoor. Just adjust it to your needs, the important thing is that its comfortable. The AC is really cool, maybe because of the cloudy factor too. The staff are friendly and professional, its just that the crew is sometimes overwhelmed when there are a lot of online orders, and onsite visitors are forced to queue longer. Uniquely, this place does not accept cash payments. Must use a card (debit/credit) or qris. There is a free wifi facility too, you can ask the officer/cashier for information if you want to use the soul promise wifi. In terms of menu... no need to ask anymore, thats fine. I like the choice of milk for some of the drink menus, you can choose soy or oat milk. For those who want to pray, the solution is to go to the nearest mosque, one option is the Ash-Shobiriin Mosque across from Mie Establishment. About 1-2 minutes from the soul appointment if you ride a motorbike Parking: Parking is quite adequate compared to visitor capacity

review_text: Angkringan ini ada di bengkel Langkah Jaya, di gmaps titiknya geser ke utara. Dan setau saya angkringan Ngudi Raos ini salah satu angkringan dg cabang yg banyak di Surabaya. Dari dulu 4-5 tahun yll sering kesini. Sebelum pandemi angkringan ini rame banget, mejanya dari pintu bengkel bisa sampe mepet pager. Apalagi malem minggu, behh rame bangett. Tapi sayang sekarang tersisa  -nya. Mungkin krn ga serame dulu, jadinya sekarang pilihan menunya ga sebanyak dulu. Dan sayangnya (lagi) beberapa sate ada yg kurang fresh. Menurut saya mgkn karena keluar masuk freezer. Krn kurang fresh, yg awalnya pgn makan sate macem2, akhirnya cuma milih 3 sate aja. Saran sih, tolong pengelola lebih memperhatikan manajemen stoknya, biar ga ada menu yg terasa kurang fresh atau malah cenderung amis.
review_translated_text: This angkringan is at the Step Jaya workshop, on gmaps the point is shifted to the north. And as far as I know, Ngudi Raos angkringan is one of the angkringan with many branches in Surabaya. Ive been coming here frequently for 4-5 years. Before the pandemic, this angkringan was very busy, the tables from the workshop door could be close to pagers. Especially on weekends, its really busy. But unfortunately now there is only   left. Maybe because its not as exciting as before, so now there arent as many menu choices as before. And unfortunately (again) some of the satay is not fresh enough. I think it might be because it goes in and out of the freezer. Because it wasnt fresh enough, those who initially wanted to eat various types of satay ended up only choosing 3 types of satay. My advice, please pay more attention to stock management, so that nothing on the menu feels less fresh or tends to be fishy.

As a burger lover, Ive tried a lot of burgers and if the expensive burgers taste really good, this is really cheap (using online promos too) only around 15 thousand/pc but it really tastes good. The seasoning is delicious, the chicken meat is thick (although the flour is quite thick), the patties taste like meat & are tender. The bun isnt very fluffy but its soft hahaha. The packaging is just paper, you know, the price is also cheap. Will repurchase for sure! Really delicious..

review_text: Udah dua kali ke sini. Yang pertama sama temen (karena rekomendasi temen sih), yang kedua sama keluarga (gantian ngerekomendasiin tempatnya). Baru tau kalau ada hidden gem kayak Parigie. Meskipun tempatnya di hotel, tapi harganya affordable. Tempatnya cozy, luas, bersih, cocok buat hangout atau nugas. Tempat parkirnya juga luas dan tiket parkirnya gak bikin keluar banyak uang (gak kayak tiket parkir stasiun). Makanannya juga lumayan enak, meskipun ada beberapa hal yang mungkin bisa diperbaiki (ini pendapat pribadi dan bersama, karena gak cuma saya pribadi yang berpikir begini). Untuk minuman, saya rekomendasikan Choco Oreo. Untuk ukuran large, menurut saya affordable di harga Rp.25.000,00. Lalu untuk makanan juga ada Nasi Dadar series, affordable juga di harga yang sama untuk ukuran nasi yang lumayan banyak (tidak terfoto di sini). Saya tidak sempat foto banyak makanan, cuma sempat foto Mie Goreng Bakso dan Sosis, yang sebenarnya Indomie pakai bakso dan sosis. Tapi sebagai sobat Indomie, tentu tidak pernah fail rasanya. Yang lucu, teman saya pesan Indomie Bangladesh tapi di menu tidak ada. Saya kaget, kok jadi semacam menu ghoib. Next time saya mau coba Indomie Bangladesh, meskipun kemarin sudah nyicip sedikit punya temen saya dan ternyata enak. Sepupu saya merekomendasikan Nasi Ayam Sambal Roa karena enak (saya belum sempat coba). Selain makanan berat, snack, dan minuman, juga ada pastry mulai dari cake, roti, dan kue kering (mungkin karena mau lebaran). Saya coba Chocolate and Matcha Cookie, rasanya enak dan kuenya empuk. Kemarin waktu ke sana lagi dapet croissant waktu ngisi review di TripAdvisor (gratis). Tapi belum sempat dicoba. Bagi yang bingung mau hangout/nugas di mana, di sini recommended banget soalnya menunya banyak dan tempatnya juga luas dan nyaman. 10/10 will come back to try more menu(s). Parking: Untuk ukuran hotel, harga tiket parkirnya termasuk affordable (Rp.3.000,00 flat untuk sepeda motor dan Rp.10.000,00 untuk mobil).
review_translated_text: Ive been here twice. The first was with a friend (because a friend recommended it), the second was with my family (in turn recommending the place). Just found out that there is a hidden gem like Parigie. Even though the place is in a hotel, the price is affordable. The place is cozy, spacious, clean, suitable for hanging out or doing work. The parking lot is also spacious and the parking ticket doesnt cost you a lot of money (unlike station parking tickets). The food is also quite good, although there are several things that could be improved (this is a personal and shared opinion, because Im not the only one who thinks this way). For drinks, I recommend Choco Oreo. For the large size, I think it is affordable at Rp. 25,000.00. Then for food there is also the Nasi Dadar series, affordable too at the same price for quite a large size of rice (not pictured here). I didnt have time to take photos of a lot of food, I only had time to take photos of Bakso and Sausage Fried Noodles, which actually Indomie uses meatballs and sausages. But as an Indomie friend, of course you never fail. Whats funny, my friend ordered Indomie Bangladesh but it wasnt there on the menu. I was surprised, how come it turned out to be a kind of supernatural menu. Next time I want to try Indomie Bangladesh, even though my friend tried a little yesterday and it turned out to be delicious. My cousin recommended Sambal Roa Chicken Rice because it was delicious (I havent had the chance to try it). Apart from heavy food, snacks and drinks, there are also pastries ranging from cakes, bread and pastries (maybe because its Eid). I tried the Chocolate and Matcha Cookie, it tasted delicious and the cake was soft. Yesterday, when I went there, I got a croissant when I wrote a review on TripAdvisor (its free). But havent had time to try it yet. For those who are confused about where to hang out/work on assignments, it is really recommended here because the menu is large and the place is also spacious and comfortable. 10/10 will come back to try more menu(s). Parking: For the size of the hotel, the parking ticket price is affordable (Rp. 3,000.00 flat for motorbikes and Rp. 10,000.00 for cars).

review_text: Pengalaman saya makan di Cafe Parigie siang ini (Senin, 10 April 2023). Saya bersama dengan 5 orang teman saya yang lainnya datang untuk makan siang di Cafe Parigie dikarenakan tertarik dengan menu yang disediakan dan komen dari influencer2. Semua berjalan normal di awal pemesanan menu, ketika saya bertanya penjelasan tentang menu ke pegawai cafe, mereka dapat menjawab dengan baik meskipun terkadang kurang ramah. Untuk minuman, waktu penyajian cepat. Kami datang ke cafe di pukul 12 namun hingga 30 menit makanan yang kami pesan tidak kunjung keluar. Saya sangat kecewa ketika makanan yang saya pesan tidak kunjung keluar dalam waktu yang hampir 1 jam (dimana teman-teman saya sudah hampir selesai makan). Ketika saya tanyakan ke pihak cafe, tidak ada jawaban yang memuaskan dan yang saya dapat info terakhir makanan baru akan dimasak disaat itu. Jawaban dan respon dari pegawai cafepun sungguh tidak memuaskan (tidak ada sedikit pun permintaan maaf dari pihak cafe). Hingga akhirnya saya memutuskan membatalkan pesanan saya dan meminta refund dikarenakan jam istirahat saya sudah hampir selesai. Untuk taste makanan yang teman saya makan (taste standard). Pelayanan (sangat kurang untuk sekelas cafe, mohon untuk ditraining semua pegawainya) Overall, menurut saya tidak untuk dikunjungi kembali dalam waktu dekat.
review_translated_text: My experience of eating at Cafe Parigie this afternoon (Monday, April 10 2023). I, along with 5 other friends, came for lunch at Cafe Parigie because they were interested in the menu provided and comments from influencers. Everything went normally at the beginning of ordering the menu, when I asked the cafe staff for an explanation about the menu, they answered well even though they were sometimes less friendly. For drinks, serving time is fast. We came to the cafe at 12 oclock but after 30 minutes the food we ordered had not come out. I was very disappointed when the food I ordered didnt come out in almost 1 hour (by which time my friends had almost finished eating). When I asked the cafe, there was no satisfactory answer and the latest information I got was that the food would only be cooked at that time. The answers and responses from the cafe employees were really unsatisfactory (there was not the slightest apology from the cafe). Until finally I decided to cancel my order and ask for a refund because my break was almost over. For the taste of the food my friends eat (taste standard). Service (very poor for cafe class, please train all employees) Overall, I dont think its worth revisiting in the near future.

review_text: Tempatnya Sederhana tp kopi butter sm bubur Ayam hainannya endul , kedai kopitiam murah tp gk murahan...Syng parkiran kurg luas, cm utk 5 motor...overall,Kalo kesini enak pas sarapan pagi2
review_translated_text: The place is simple but the coffee is buttery and the Hainanese chicken porridge is delicious, the kopitiam shop is cheap but not cheap...The parking lot isnt big enough for 5 motorbikes...overall, if you come here its good for breakfast

review_text: seandainya bs kasih semua bintang di langit, kukasih     tp disini hanya bs kasih bintang 5. enak bgt!!! murah     dan ak sukanya, yg nyiapin pesenan itu teliti bgt dan sesuai request. ak request kopinya gula dikit aja, toast selai dikit. dan disajikan manisnya pas bgt sesuai seleraku    (pengalaman d tmpt lain sering bgt dah request less sugar, tp dikasihnya ttp kemanisen   ) sangat recomended pokoknya.
review_translated_text: If I could give you all the stars in the sky, I would give it     but here I can only give you 5 stars. So delicious!!! cheap     and I like it, the person who prepared the order was very careful and according to request. I requested just a little sugar for the coffee, a little jam for the toast. and it was served sweet, just right for my taste    (experience at other places where I often ask for less sugar, but I still give it sweetness   ) I really recommend it.

review_text: tempat nyaman, makanan enak ga terlalu mahal juga, cuma kurang tempat parkir

review_text: Letaknya depan Ramayana dept store/ sebelah optic mc, jadi kalo dari pdam delta setelah rel kereta segera merapat ke kiri :) Kopitiam butter enak, ga terlalu manis Teh tariknya juga oke,  disini real teh tarik bukan pake teh tarik instan ( bisa liat langsung proses buatnya) Roti srikaya : Mayan spt roti2 bakar pada umumnya hanya saja basenya pake butter bukan mentega
review_translated_text: Its located in front of the Ramayana dept store/next to Optical MC, so if youre coming from PDAM Delta after the train tracks, immediately turn left :) Kopitiam butter is delicious, not too sweet The Teh Tarik is also good, here its real Teh Tarik, not instant Tartan tea (you can see the process of making it directly) Srikaya bread: Mayan is like toasted bread in general, only the base is butter instead of butter

review_text: Tempatnya nyaman, enak, bersih. Minumannya enak banget, aku pesen teh tarik rasanya enak poll. Kopi butter nya juga enak, beda dari yang lain. Pokoknya tempat ini worth it lahh.
review_translated_text: The place is comfortable, nice, clean. The drinks are really delicious, I ordered the Teh Tarik, it tastes delicious poll. The butter coffee is also delicious, different from the others. Anyway, this place is worth it.

review_text: Highly recommended, tp memang untuk pelayanan agak memakan waktu ya? Padahal hanya pesan bubur sama kopi dan parkirnya agak sulit. Tp selebihnya enak. Worth to try bgt makanan di resto ini. Semoga jam bukanya bisa lebih lama sedikit hehe.

review_text: Kesini harus pagi.. Soalnya jam 14.00 sudah tutup. Jadi baru bisa mampir pas weekend aja. Udah nyoba bubur ayam hainan, nasi ayam hainan, choco toast. Enak semua cocok dilidah. Kalo minuman nyoba teh tarik nya sooo yummy.. Definitely will back and try the other menu.
review_translated_text: You have to come here early... Because at 14.00 it closes. So I can only stop by on weekends. Ive tried Hainanese chicken porridge, Hainanese chicken rice, choco toast. Everything is delicious and fits the palate. If you want to drink, try the Teh Tarik, its sooo yummy.. Definitely will go back and try the other menu.

review_text: Cheap price. It feels okay. Food service takes a long time. Just order 2 portions of porridge and 1 pulled tea, it takes up to 25 minutes to prepare. Need a speed up again?

review_text: Resto yang membudayakan kopitiam. Terletak dijantung kota sidoarjo, tempat ini menawarkan suasana kopitiam. Tidak hanya kopi, tersedia juga coklat dan teh. Kopinya khas kopitiqm banget. Pilihan makanan serba hainan beragam mulai dari nasi, mie, kwetiau bahkan bubur. Untuk makanan ringan tersedia roti toast dan cakwe. Buka 06.00 siap menemani ngopi pagimu. Parking: Mobil parkir di Ramayana
review_translated_text: The restaurant that cultivates kopitiam. Located in the heart of Sidoarjo city, this place offers a kopitiam atmosphere. Not only coffee, chocolate and tea are also available. The coffee is really typical kopitiqm. The choice of Hainan food varies from rice, noodles, kwetiau and even porridge. For snacks, toast and cakwe are available. Opens 06.00 ready to accompany your morning coffee. Parking: Car parking at Ramayana

Mantap sih, harganya juga nggak mahal, dapet telor pula. Kapan-kapan mau pesen lagi lewat ojol kalo ga sempat ke sana.

review_translated_text: When I want to go to the toll road, I see Nasimura, its interesting, the style of the place looks like Japan. It turns out that the food concept is Japanese wrapped rice. So there is a menu of ciken katsu, beef Yakiniku, satay yakitori. Just ordered a lot and wanted to try them all. Im sure my favorite is beef, but the most impressive is the SAMBEL! Keep adding rice. Luckily they sell cold drinks too. Its great, the price is not expensive, you get eggs too. Sometime I want to order again via ojol if I dont have time to go there.

review_text: Mencoba minuman baru milik YouTubers kondang Nex Carlos yang hadir di Sidoarjo. Penasaran banget krn katanya utk bikin bobanya sampe riset dan berkunjung ke Taiwan lho!! Lokasinya ada di tengah kota Sidoarjo tepatnya di depan Polres Sidoarjo lama, warna container boxnya yang mencolok memudahkan untuk mencari lokasi Minum cui. Variannya ada banyak mulai dari lemon, taro, strawberry, matcha, Milo sampai yang legend yaitu brown sugar milk dan milk tea jug ada. Untuk bobanya ada 2 macam yg brown sama leci. Utk rasanya seger, manisnya pas, tekstur bobanya lebih ke lembut tapi tidak terlalu kenyal banget, tapi tetap ada perlawanan di mulut. Untuk harga standar sih, tapi karena ada promo buy 1 get 1 sampai 26 September 2021 jadi mending buruan beli deh!!
review_translated_text: Try a new drink from famous YouTubers Nex Carlos who is present in Sidoarjo. I was really curious because it was said to make boba until I researched it and visited Taiwan, you know!! The location is in the middle of Sidoarjo city, precisely in front of the old Sidoarjo Police Station. The striking color of the container box makes it easy to find the location for drinking cui. There are many variants, from lemon, taro, strawberry, matcha, Milo to the legendary ones, namely brown sugar milk and milk tea. For boba, there are 2 types, brown and lychee. The taste is fresh, the sweetness is just right, the texture of the boba is more soft but not too chewy, but there is still resistance in the mouth. Its a standard price, but because there is a buy 1 get 1 promotion until 26 September 2021, its better to hurry up and buy it!!

review_text: Baru buka nih di Sidoarjo. Kmren nyobain beli Bobba brown sugar milk tea (18k) Tidak terlalu manis, suka sih karena aku gak suka yang muanis banget. Udah dapet dari manisnya boba. Cheesy bobba brown sugar fresh milk (23k) Creamy banget, ada asin2nya. Manis tapi masih oke. Overall oke, bobanya bukan tipe kenyel2 gitu, agak overcooked tapi suka    soalnya males nguyah kalo terlalu kenyal. Sayangnya di sini, lama pelayanannya. Mungkin masih baru ya..
review_translated_text: Just opened in Sidoarjo. Then try buying it Bobba brown sugar milk tea (18k) Not too sweet, I like it because I dont like very sweet things. Already got the sweetness of boba. Cheesy bobba brown sugar fresh milk (23k) Very creamy, theres a lot of saltiness in it. Sweet but still okay. Overall its okay, the boba isnt the chewy type, its a bit overcooked but I like it    because Im too lazy to eat it if its too chewy. Unfortunately here, the service takes a long time. Maybe its still new...

Pengalaman sangat tidak menyenangkan! Saya habis antar anak saya sekolah dekat situ, dan cari tempat duduk untuk kerja sebentar. Saat itu jam 7an. Saya lihat di google map kalau tempat ini buka jam 9. Dari 10 booth, hanya 5 yg kelihatan ada isinya. Saya tunggu kedai buka disana duduk sambil minum minuman saya. Ada beberapa yang duduk juga. Dan tiba2 ada mbak2 datang atur2 printer atau apalah di meja (saya pikir oh sudah datang yang jualan). Dan ada serombobgan keluarga datang dengan bayi. Mereka dengan sopan tanya apakah boleh duduk disitu. Mbak2 ini dengan lantang bilang tidak boleh, kalau tidak beli disana. Yang (lagi) duduk disana itu orang bebal..Bahkan duduk menunggu juga tidak boleh (kira2 begitu yang saya tangkap). Saya yang ga sengaja dengar langsung kaget. Lha belum pada buka, masak tidak boleh menunggu disitu? Bapak2 itu ngamuk dan pergi sambil sedikit mengumpat. Saya juga langsung beres-beres, tidak jadi mau beli disana. Lainnya juga pergi. Padahal niat nyobain menu2nya..sayang sekali. Baru kali ini saya alami hal seperti ini. Sangat mengecewakan...
review_translated_text: Very unpleasant experience! I had finished taking my child to school nearby, and was looking for a place to sit down to work for a while. It was 7 oclock. I saw on Google map that this place opens at 9. Of the 10 booths, only 5 seemed to have any contents. I waited for the shop to open and sat there drinking my drink. There were some sitting too. And suddenly a lady came to set up a printer or something on the table (I thought oh the sales person has come). And there were a bunch of families coming with babies. They politely asked if they could sit there. These ladies loudly said no, if you dont buy there. The one (who is) sitting there is an idiot... Even sitting and waiting is not allowed (thats what I think). I accidentally heard it and was immediately shocked. Well, its not open yet, so you cant wait there? The men got angry and left while cursing a little. I also immediately cleaned it up, so I didnt want to buy there. Others also left. Even though I wanted to try the menu... its a shame. This is the first time I have experienced something like this. Very disappointing...
